Well, that's certainly the most ridiculous thing I've heard today.<br>
<br>
Speaking as someone with 10 years experience in face-to-face Live Action Roleplaying I can say that it is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>essential</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to differentiate between IC and OOC if, at any time, any participant is confused as to the IC status of a conversation.  It is the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>only</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> way to ensure no one is inadvertantly insulted.<br>
<br>
Now as to rerolling being a fresh slate.  Well, I've always felt it should be except in rare cases where you play a son or brother of thre deceased character.<br>
<br>
If I return to EQ (I actually got it running again last night by reinstalling the drivers that origianlly came with my video card) I will start as a new character and not RP old friendships.  If players who knew me before do anything to help me out that will have to be taken OOC. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hateschild>Hates Child</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/24/03 11:27:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3082.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   closing thoughts</span><hr size=1> didn't do anything to her, in this life or any other. she has some imagination and has fabriacated things to a far out proportion. and solandeb was responding to someoen else who said she had some heart ache at lvl 20 or something, that it was him at that time.  <br>
